com.i2group.apollo.model.builders
Interface IBuilder<T>

Type Parameters:
T - The type of object that this builder creates.
All Known Implementing Classes:
BinaryDocumentPropertyValueBuilder, CompoundPropertyValueBuilder, DatePropertyValueBuilder, DateTimePropertyValueBuilder, GeospatialPropertyValueBuilder, SimplePropertyValueBuilder, TimePropertyValueBuilder, XmlPropertyValueBuilder
public interface IBuilder<T>

A builder for creating objects to be used in the Intelligence Analysis Platform.

Unless documented otherwise, assume that an IBuilder is not thread-safe.

Since:
5.0

Method Detail

build

T build()
Validates the data in the builder, and then creates and returns the object.

Note: The builder performs some validation of the object that it creates, but the object is not guaranteed to pass server validation.

Returns:
See above.

populate

IBuilder<T> populate(T object)
Populates the data in the builder from an object of the same type that the builder creates.

Assuming an implementation of T.equals(), then after this statement:

t2 = builder.populate(t1).build();

The following expressions should both evaluate to true:

t2.equals(t1) == true
(t2 == t1) == false

Parameters:
object - The object from which to populate the builder.
Returns:
The builder, populated with the data from the specified object.
